definitions.definition: A territorial authority in Waikato region, New Zealand , with its main towns being Cambridge and Te Awamutu ; in full, Waipa District .
A river in Waikato region, New Zealand , which joins the Waikato River at Ngaruawahia ; in full, Waipa River .
